# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Duncit Monorepo — root .env.example
#
# This file documents the *common* env shape used by every Duncit web app
# (mweb, admin, partners-app, ads, crm, finance, tech). Each workspace has its
# own .env.example with its specific overrides. Local development does NOT
# require any of these to be set — `vite dev` defaults every URL to
# http://localhost:2001/graphql (the local server) and the production build
# defaults to https://server.duncit.com/graphql.
#
# Service ports (local dev):
#   Website        : 2000   https://duncit.com
#   Server         : 2001   https://server.duncit.com
#   Admin          : 2002   https://admin.duncit.com
#   mWeb           : 2003   https://mweb.duncit.com
#   Partners App   : 2005   https://partners-app.duncit.com
#   Ads            : 2006   https://ads.duncit.com
#   CRM            : 2007   https://crm.duncit.com
#   Finance        : 2008   https://finance.duncit.com
#   Tech           : 2009   https://tech.duncit.com
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Server-only: Google OAuth credentials used to verify id_tokens server-side.
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret_here

# Web-app: same client ID is shared across every workspace. Copy this same
# value into mweb-app/.env, admin/.env, partners-app/.env, ads/.env,
# crm/.env, finance/.env and tech/.env (or set it once in your shell).
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here

# Optional dev override (otherwise dev = localhost, build = production).
# VITE_GRAPHQL_URL=http://localhost:2001/graphql

# ─── CRM calling (Twilio webhooks reaching localhost) ───
# Server-only. On a LOCAL server start we auto-open a free ngrok tunnel so
# Twilio can reach the /twilio/* voice webhooks (it can't hit localhost). Get a
# free token at https://dashboard.ngrok.com/get-started/your-authtoken
# NGROK_AUTHTOKEN=your_free_ngrok_authtoken
#
# Optional explicit override for the webhook base URL (wins over auto/ngrok),
# e.g. a fixed tunnel domain. In prod this defaults to https://server.duncit.com
# TWILIO_WEBHOOK_BASE_URL=https://your-tunnel.ngrok-free.app
